1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:06,960
a:padam apaharta:ram da:ta:ram
sarvasampadam

2
00:00:07,000 --> 00:00:19,000
lo:ka:bhi:ra:mam Shri:ra:mam bhu:yo bhu:yo
nama:myaham

3
00:00:23,000 --> 00:00:25,000
Jai Shri:man Na:ra:yana!

4
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:30,000
Dear devotees of Bhagava:n,

5
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:38,000
when we start a task,

6
00:00:39,000 --> 00:00:42,000
for what reason are we undertaking it,

7
00:00:43,000 --> 00:00:45,000
What is its purpose?

8
00:00:46,000 --> 00:00:48,000
Who all are involved in it?

9
00:00:49,000 --> 00:00:50,960
What should we do?

10
00:00:51,000 --> 00:00:56,000
Only after knowing these do we start the
work.

11
00:00:57,000 --> 00:01:04,000
In the same way, if we want to study a
scripture,

12
00:01:05,000 --> 00:01:07,000
why should we read it?

13
00:01:08,000 --> 00:01:10,000
What should we know?

14
00:01:11,000 --> 00:01:14,960
What is the benefit of reading it?

15
00:01:15,000 --> 00:01:23,000
If we understand this and feel it is
beneficial,

16
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:29,000
then we can choose to read it or something
else.

17
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:32,000
The 'Bhagavad Gi:tha' too,

18
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:37,000
for whom is it intended?

19
00:01:38,000 --> 00:01:40,000
and what is it meant to teach?

20
00:01:41,000 --> 00:01:45,000
We should understand this before starting
to read the 'Bhagavad Gi:tha'.

21
00:01:46,000 --> 00:01:55,000
Usually, everyone says the Bhagavad Gi:tha
is a very great scripture,

22
00:01:57,000 --> 00:02:00,000
but what is its purpose?

23
00:02:01,000 --> 00:02:02,960
For whom is the 'Bhagavad Gi:tha' meant?

24
00:02:03,000 --> 00:02:14,584
It covers business management, personality
development, science, philosophy,

25
00:02:14,624 --> 00:02:16,000
theology.

26
00:02:17,000 --> 00:02:22,000
There are also many morals and other
teachings.

27
00:02:23,000 --> 00:02:26,960
We often discuss the 'Bhagavad Gi:tha',

28
00:02:27,000 --> 00:02:32,000
but when we actually approach that
scripture,

29
00:02:33,000 --> 00:02:36,000
what should we learn from it?

30
00:02:37,000 --> 00:02:39,000
What is it that we need to understand?

31
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:42,000
If we have a clear understanding,

32
00:02:43,000 --> 00:02:46,000
we try to understand it from that
perspective.

33
00:02:49,000 --> 00:02:56,000
If we call a Prime Minister and ask him to
clear the roads,

34
00:02:57,000 --> 00:03:00,000
he can indeed clear the roads.

35
00:03:01,000 --> 00:03:04,000
He might even have cleaned them himself.

36
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:07,000
But if the purpose is just to clear the
roads,

37
00:03:08,000 --> 00:03:10,000
we don't actually need him for that task.

38
00:03:11,000 --> 00:03:16,000
as there is someone else assigned to that
task.

39
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:20,960
there are some things that only this
person can do,

40
00:03:21,000 --> 00:03:28,000
When the main benefit is to receive those
unique things from him,

41
00:03:29,000 --> 00:03:33,000
then we must approach him for that
purpose.

42
00:03:34,000 --> 00:03:38,000
Apart from that, when someone speaks or
acts,

43
00:03:39,000 --> 00:03:42,000
whether it is good or bad,

44
00:03:43,000 --> 00:03:45,000
it shows us the ignorance or incapacity we
carry.

45
00:03:46,000 --> 00:03:51,000
This awareness lets us recognize

46
00:03:52,000 --> 00:03:55,000
the nature of our ignorance.

47
00:03:56,000 --> 00:04:03,000
Now, when we present a scripture like the
Bhagavad Gi:tha,

48
00:04:04,000 --> 00:04:06,000
what is its purpose?

49
00:04:07,000 --> 00:04:09,000
Is it only to teach science?

50
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:13,000
To teach science, we need scientific
books,

51
00:04:14,000 --> 00:04:16,000
and we can follow those happily.

52
00:04:17,000 --> 00:04:18,000
learning all those things from them.

53
00:04:19,000 --> 00:04:22,960
Is it necessary to take the 'Bhagavad
Gi:tha' and learn from it?

54
00:04:23,000 --> 00:04:25,000
No, we do not.

55
00:04:26,000 --> 00:04:29,000
To learn morals,

56
00:04:30,000 --> 00:04:33,000
we need books that teach morals,

57
00:04:34,000 --> 00:04:38,000
We can go to them and learn those
principles comfortably.

58
00:04:39,000 --> 00:04:45,000
Is the 'Bhagavad Gi:tha' meant to teach us
management skills?

59
00:04:46,000 --> 00:04:49,960
There are many management courses,

60
00:04:50,000 --> 00:04:52,000
and if we go there happily,

61
00:04:53,000 --> 00:04:55,000
they will teach us all the details about
it.

62
00:04:56,000 --> 00:04:57,000
we can learn from them.

63
00:04:58,000 --> 00:05:01,000
Is it meant to teach us dietary rules?

64
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:07,000
There are so many doctors and physicians,

65
00:05:08,000 --> 00:05:10,000
we can learn from them.

66
00:05:11,000 --> 00:05:12,000
Through them we can also gain such
knowledge.

67
00:05:13,000 --> 00:05:19,000
The question is not whether the Bhagavad
Gi:tha teaches this or not,

68
00:05:20,000 --> 00:05:25,000
but if we understand the main goal of the
Bhagavad Gi:tha,

69
00:05:26,000 --> 00:05:29,000
then wherever we go, whatever we see,

70
00:05:30,000 --> 00:05:33,000
we should ask if it leads us toward that
goal or not.

71
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:37,960
Or are we able to attain that goal through
it?

72
00:05:38,000 --> 00:05:40,000
It is our responsibility to know that

73
00:05:41,000 --> 00:05:43,000
That is why it is our responsibility to
know it,

74
00:05:44,000 --> 00:05:48,000
and understand the main purpose of the
'Bhagavad Gi:tha'.

75
00:05:49,000 --> 00:05:51,000
One aspect is to make Arjuna aware of his
duty.

76
00:05:52,000 --> 00:05:55,000
That was set forth as a key objective.

77
00:05:56,000 --> 00:05:59,000
It was begun for that very purpose.

78
00:06:00,000 --> 00:06:03,000
mainly for that reason alone.

79
00:06:04,000 --> 00:06:07,000
If it were only to instruct Arjuna,

80
00:06:08,000 --> 00:06:10,000
then once he was taught, the task was
done.

81
00:06:11,000 --> 00:06:13,000
There would be nothing more needed.

82
00:06:14,000 --> 00:06:17,000
For our times, nothing beyond that would
be required.

83
00:06:18,000 --> 00:06:24,000
No, it would have remained confined to
that situation alone.

84
00:06:25,000 --> 00:06:27,000
But the 'Bhagavad Gi:tha'

85
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:31,000
It is not a scripture meant only for
Arjuna,

86
00:06:32,000 --> 00:06:35,000
nor solely to urge him into battle.

87
00:06:36,000 --> 00:06:39,000
Then, for what purpose was it given?

88
00:06:40,000 --> 00:06:43,000
It is for the human race.

89
00:06:44,000 --> 00:06:46,000
When they are born on this earth,

90
00:06:47,000 --> 00:06:49,000
before they die,

91
00:06:50,000 --> 00:06:54,000
if they understand and do the duties they
must,

92
00:06:55,000 --> 00:06:58,000
those actions become truly worthy.

93
00:06:59,000 --> 00:07:00,000
This must be conveyed.

94
00:07:01,000 --> 00:07:04,000
How should those duties be performed?

95
00:07:05,000 --> 00:07:07,000
This guidance is essential

96
00:07:08,000 --> 00:07:10,000
for all of humanity.

97
00:07:11,000 --> 00:07:14,000
How should one’s dedication be?

98
00:07:15,000 --> 00:07:18,000
It is crucial for a human being to
understand

99
00:07:19,000 --> 00:07:21,000
that saying this

100
00:07:22,000 --> 00:07:27,000
is the main purpose of Krishna's
incarnation in this world.

101
00:07:28,000 --> 00:07:29,960
Arjuna,

102
00:07:30,000 --> 00:07:32,000
using a certain pretext,

103
00:07:33,000 --> 00:07:35,000
was part of a plan,

104
00:07:36,000 --> 00:07:38,000
and through him, Krishna fulfilled it.

105
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:42,000
This is what we should understand.

106
00:07:43,000 --> 00:07:45,000
There are other points as well.

107
00:07:46,000 --> 00:07:47,000
yuktha:ha:ra viha:rasya,

108
00:07:48,000 --> 00:07:50,000
learn how to eat properly.

109
00:07:51,000 --> 00:07:53,000
yuktha svapna:vabo:dha:sya,

110
00:07:54,000 --> 00:07:56,000
they say, be regulated in sleep and
wakefulness.

111
00:07:57,000 --> 00:07:59,000
Such guidelines are mentioned.

112
00:08:00,000 --> 00:08:03,000
There are other rules,

113
00:08:04,000 --> 00:08:06,000
but to explain those rules,

114
00:08:07,000 --> 00:08:09,000
what is their purpose?

115
00:08:10,000 --> 00:08:13,000
What is the duty of a human being?

116
00:08:14,000 --> 00:08:16,000
What should a person actually perform?

117
00:08:17,000 --> 00:08:19,000
For the common man,

118
00:08:20,000 --> 00:08:23,000
the Bhagavad Gi:tha came to teach this.

119
00:08:24,000 --> 00:08:26,000
That is why the 'Bhagavad Gi:tha'

120
00:08:27,000 --> 00:08:29,000
is divided into three parts.

121
00:08:30,000 --> 00:08:32,000
The first part consists of six chapters.

122
00:08:33,000 --> 00:08:35,000
The second part also consists of six
chapters,

123
00:08:36,000 --> 00:08:38,000
and the third part has six chapters as
well.

124
00:08:39,000 --> 00:08:42,000
Altogether, the scripture has eighteen
chapters.

125
00:08:43,000 --> 00:08:45,000
The first six chapters

126
00:08:46,000 --> 00:08:51,000
aim to reveal the true nature of the soul.

127
00:08:52,000 --> 00:08:54,000
We don't find these teachings elsewhere,

128
00:08:55,000 --> 00:08:56,960
not in management courses,

129
00:08:57,000 --> 00:08:59,000
not in moral teachings,

130
00:09:00,000 --> 00:09:02,000
not in scientific studies,

131
00:09:03,000 --> 00:09:06,000
nor in any other places.

132
00:09:07,000 --> 00:09:09,000
It is given for us to understand this
truth.

133
00:09:10,000 --> 00:09:12,000
We should at least come closer to it.

134
00:09:13,000 --> 00:09:15,000
To approach the 'Bhagavad Gi:tha',

135
00:09:16,000 --> 00:09:17,000
you need to seek it out,

136
00:09:18,000 --> 00:09:19,000
There is no need to complain that it is
not being taught.

137
00:09:20,000 --> 00:09:21,960
if you don't know the 'Bhagavad Gi:tha',

138
00:09:22,000 --> 00:09:24,000
there is no reason to criticize them.

139
00:09:25,000 --> 00:09:27,000
We need not go searching for faults,

140
00:09:28,000 --> 00:09:30,000
because the scripture itself will reach
us.

141
00:09:31,000 --> 00:09:33,000
The first six chapters

142
00:09:34,000 --> 00:09:36,000
are called 'A:thma Shatkam'.

143
00:09:37,000 --> 00:09:41,000
They provide a detailed description of the
a:thma thatthva.

144
00:09:42,000 --> 00:09:44,000
The second six chapters

145
00:09:45,000 --> 00:09:48,000
are called 'Bhakti Shatkam'.

146
00:09:49,000 --> 00:09:51,000
Bhakti means love,

147
00:09:52,000 --> 00:09:55,000
This love must be directed towards a
certain thatthva.

148
00:09:56,000 --> 00:09:58,000
It should be towards Bhagava:n, as the
Bhagavad Gi:tha teaches.

149
00:09:59,000 --> 00:10:00,000
Who is this Bhagava:n in the Gi:tha?

150
00:10:01,000 --> 00:10:02,000
What is his nature?

151
00:10:03,000 --> 00:10:04,000
Where does he reside?

152
00:10:05,000 --> 00:10:06,000
What actions does he perform?

153
00:10:07,000 --> 00:10:08,000
What is your relationship with him?

154
00:10:09,000 --> 00:10:10,000
What is your duty towards him?

155
00:10:11,000 --> 00:10:13,000
What do you expect from him?

156
00:10:14,000 --> 00:10:15,000
To what extent is that achievable?

157
00:10:16,000 --> 00:10:17,000
These must be understood well,

158
00:10:18,000 --> 00:10:19,000
and to explain them,

159
00:10:20,000 --> 00:10:24,000
The six chapters in the middle of the
'Bhagavad Gi:tha'

160
00:10:25,000 --> 00:10:27,000
are called the Bhakti Shatkam.

161
00:10:28,000 --> 00:10:30,000
This is the name of the second Shatkam.

162
00:10:31,000 --> 00:10:32,000
After saying this,

163
00:10:33,000 --> 00:10:37,000
Arjuna had some doubts.

164
00:10:38,000 --> 00:10:40,000
He thought, if I speak of these,

165
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:42,000
can I solve this?

166
00:10:43,000 --> 00:10:43,960
With that courage arising,

167
00:10:44,000 --> 00:10:45,000
after expressing it,

168
00:10:46,000 --> 00:10:47,000
the first six chapters,

169
00:10:48,000 --> 00:10:49,000
The six chapters, out of the twelve,

170
00:10:50,000 --> 00:10:51,000
were arranged once again in order,

171
00:10:52,000 --> 00:10:54,000
and condensed systematically.

172
00:10:55,000 --> 00:10:56,000
Wherever there were gaps,

173
00:10:57,000 --> 00:11:00,000
or pauses here and there,

174
00:11:01,000 --> 00:11:02,000
and any points to be filled,

175
00:11:03,000 --> 00:11:04,000
all of those were gathered

176
00:11:05,000 --> 00:11:06,000
he combined all of them.

177
00:11:07,000 --> 00:11:08,000
To present everything in full,

178
00:11:09,000 --> 00:11:09,960
the last six chapters,

179
00:11:10,000 --> 00:11:11,000
were given the name

180
00:11:12,000 --> 00:11:14,000
Purva Sesham.

181
00:11:15,000 --> 00:11:16,000
Purva se:sham,

182
00:11:17,000 --> 00:11:18,000
the remainder of what was said earlier,

183
00:11:19,000 --> 00:11:20,000
that is what it was named.

184
00:11:21,000 --> 00:11:22,000
In this way,

185
00:11:23,000 --> 00:11:24,000
it was presented

186
00:11:25,000 --> 00:11:27,000
he divided it into three parts.

187
00:11:28,000 --> 00:11:29,000
The scripture of eighteen chapters,

188
00:11:30,000 --> 00:11:31,000
using Arjuna

189
00:11:32,000 --> 00:11:33,000
as the one

190
00:11:34,000 --> 00:11:34,960
for whom the reason was set,

191
00:11:35,000 --> 00:11:36,000
Sri: Krushna

192
00:11:37,000 --> 00:11:38,000
gave this teaching.

193
00:11:39,000 --> 00:11:40,000
It is a very revered scripture,

194
00:11:41,000 --> 00:11:42,000
an Adhya:thma scripture,

195
00:11:43,000 --> 00:11:44,000
the Bhagavad Gi:tha.

196
00:11:45,000 --> 00:11:46,000
In it,

197
00:11:47,000 --> 00:11:48,000
the first four chapters

198
00:11:49,000 --> 00:11:51,000
explain

199
00:11:53,000 --> 00:11:54,000
the sorrow

200
00:11:56,000 --> 00:11:57,000
Arjuna's heart.

201
00:11:58,000 --> 00:11:59,000
That

202
00:12:00,000 --> 00:12:01,000
soka

203
00:12:02,000 --> 00:12:03,000
or Visha:da

204
00:12:04,000 --> 00:12:05,000
is described.

205
00:12:06,000 --> 00:12:07,000
His power of vive:chana was lost,

206
00:12:08,000 --> 00:12:09,000
that is, the capacity to discern.

207
00:12:10,000 --> 00:12:11,000
Vive:chana means

208
00:12:12,000 --> 00:12:13,000
the ability to analyze.

209
00:12:14,000 --> 00:12:15,000
The capacity was reduced.

210
00:12:16,000 --> 00:12:18,000
What should be analyzed?

211
00:12:19,000 --> 00:12:20,000
One must discern the body

212
00:12:21,000 --> 00:12:22,000
the a:thma,

213
00:12:23,000 --> 00:12:24,000
to see them separately,

214
00:12:25,000 --> 00:12:26,000
to recognize their difference.

215
00:12:27,000 --> 00:12:28,000
This discernment is crucial

216
00:12:29,000 --> 00:12:30,000
to benefit from the sa:dhanas.

217
00:12:31,000 --> 00:12:32,000
He spoke of seven sa:dhanas:

218
00:12:33,000 --> 00:12:34,000
vimoka,

219
00:12:35,000 --> 00:12:35,960
vimo:ka,

220
00:12:36,000 --> 00:12:36,960
abhya:sa,

221
00:12:37,000 --> 00:12:37,960
kriya,

222
00:12:38,000 --> 00:12:38,960
anava:sa:da,

223
00:12:39,000 --> 00:12:39,960
kalya:na, and anudharsha.

224
00:12:40,000 --> 00:12:40,960
In this way,

225
00:12:41,000 --> 00:12:42,000
He told us about seven sa:dhanas.

226
00:12:43,000 --> 00:12:43,960
Among those seven sa:dhanas,

227
00:12:44,000 --> 00:12:45,000
the very first sa:dhana

228
00:12:46,000 --> 00:12:48,000
He started with is vive:kam.

229
00:12:49,000 --> 00:12:51,000
Vive:kam means intelligence.

230
00:12:52,000 --> 00:12:53,000
No,

231
00:12:54,000 --> 00:12:54,960
vive:kam means

232
00:12:55,000 --> 00:12:57,000
the ability to separate and see.

233
00:12:58,000 --> 00:12:58,960
That is the meaning of

234
00:12:59,000 --> 00:13:00,000
vive:chana.

235
00:13:01,000 --> 00:13:03,000
What should be done in vive:chana?

236
00:13:05,000 --> 00:13:06,000
That is,

237
00:13:07,000 --> 00:13:07,960
the body

238
00:13:08,000 --> 00:13:08,960
and the a:thma.

239
00:13:09,000 --> 00:13:10,000
These two are different.

240
00:13:11,000 --> 00:13:12,000
We must begin from this understanding.

241
00:13:13,000 --> 00:13:14,000
How do we understand this?

242
00:13:15,000 --> 00:13:16,000
how to identify the first sa:dhana?

243
00:13:17,000 --> 00:13:18,960
If the food you eat is good,

244
00:13:19,000 --> 00:13:19,960
everything will be good.

245
00:13:20,000 --> 00:13:22,000
The food you eat should indeed be good.

246
00:13:23,000 --> 00:13:23,960
If your thoughts are good,

247
00:13:24,000 --> 00:13:25,000
first, you should put good food inside.

248
00:13:26,000 --> 00:13:27,000
The 'indhanam' should be good.

249
00:13:28,000 --> 00:13:29,000
'Indhanam' is the food we eat.

250
00:13:30,000 --> 00:13:32,000
So, take in good food, dear one.

251
00:13:33,000 --> 00:13:35,000
What do we mean by good food?

252
00:13:36,000 --> 00:13:36,960
On what does that depend?

253
00:13:37,000 --> 00:13:38,000
So we judge the quality of the food we
take.

254
00:13:39,000 --> 00:13:40,000
We decide based on whether it is

255
00:13:43,000 --> 00:13:43,960
sa:thvikam,

256
00:13:44,000 --> 00:13:44,960
ra:jasam,

257
00:13:45,000 --> 00:13:46,000
or ta:masam.

258
00:13:47,000 --> 00:13:49,000
We must keep these distinctions in mind.

259
00:13:50,000 --> 00:13:50,960
Whatever is not good,

260
00:13:51,000 --> 00:13:52,000
we should put it aside.

261
00:13:53,000 --> 00:13:53,960
Whatever is necessary,

262
00:13:54,000 --> 00:13:55,000
we should accept it.

263
00:13:56,000 --> 00:13:56,960
And the food we eat,

264
00:13:57,000 --> 00:13:57,960
the food we eat

265
00:13:58,000 --> 00:13:59,000
The influence of food,

266
00:14:01,000 --> 00:14:03,000
the thoughts that arise in you,

267
00:14:04,000 --> 00:14:04,960
this body,

268
00:14:05,000 --> 00:14:05,960
this a:thma,

269
00:14:06,000 --> 00:14:06,960
these two,

270
00:14:07,000 --> 00:14:08,000
if we can analyze and see them separately,

271
00:14:09,000 --> 00:14:09,960
then it is called

272
00:14:10,000 --> 00:14:11,000
vivekam.

273
00:14:13,000 --> 00:14:14,000
We begin with what is called aahaara
suddhi.

274
00:14:15,000 --> 00:14:16,000
We start with this.

275
00:14:19,000 --> 00:14:19,960
Even in our scriptures,

276
00:14:20,000 --> 00:14:21,000
it is mentioned in various ways.

277
00:14:22,000 --> 00:14:23,000
Aahaara Suddho, [[REVIEW: non-Gi:tha recited verse (Chandogya 7.26.2, spans cues 277-283); confirm Sanskrit transliteration + translation with a qualified Sri:vaishnava scholar]]

278
00:14:24,000 --> 00:14:24,960
Sattva Suddhi,

279
00:14:25,000 --> 00:14:26,000
sathva suddhau,

280
00:14:27,000 --> 00:14:28,000
Dhruva Smruthi,

281
00:14:29,000 --> 00:14:29,960
Smruthi Lambe,

282
00:14:30,000 --> 00:14:31,000
Sarva Grandhinam,

283
00:14:32,000 --> 00:14:33,000
Vipramoksha.

284
00:14:36,000 --> 00:14:37,000
First, when food is pure,

285
00:14:38,000 --> 00:14:39,000
then sathva, the inner quality, becomes
pure.

286
00:14:40,000 --> 00:14:41,000
With sathva purified,

287
00:14:42,000 --> 00:14:42,960
the mind is pure.

288
00:14:43,000 --> 00:14:44,000
Sattva means mind.

289
00:14:45,000 --> 00:14:45,960
When the food is good, the mind becomes
good.

290
00:14:46,000 --> 00:14:47,000
And why should the mind be good?

291
00:14:49,000 --> 00:14:50,000
Because, Bha:rata,

292
00:14:51,000 --> 00:14:52,000
Sattva Suddho,

293
00:14:53,000 --> 00:14:54,000
Dhruva Smruthi,

294
00:14:55,000 --> 00:14:56,000
through a pure mind, jna:na flows to you.

295
00:14:58,000 --> 00:14:58,960
For that reason,

296
00:14:59,000 --> 00:14:59,960
this jna:na

297
00:15:00,000 --> 00:15:08,960
must spread smoothly, without any dirt or
obstruction within it.

298
00:15:09,000 --> 00:15:14,960
The dhara, the shrotas, should be clean.

299
00:15:15,000 --> 00:15:20,960
Then the stream of jna:na will flow freely
like water.

300
00:15:21,000 --> 00:15:35,960
If the flow of the prasadam goes on
smoothly, then it is called dhruva
smruthi.

301
00:15:36,000 --> 00:15:40,960
It is the remembrance that becomes firmly
established within us.

302
00:15:41,000 --> 00:15:47,960
When it proceeds in this way, doubts
inside are cleared,

303
00:15:48,000 --> 00:15:50,960
all knots are untied and the true nature
is realized.

304
00:15:51,000 --> 00:15:56,960
You will attain what you are meant to
attain.

305
00:15:57,000 --> 00:16:02,000
As a human, you will gain what you are
born to achieve.

306
00:16:03,000 --> 00:16:10,960
All the knots of karma are cut away, and
you gain true freedom.

307
00:16:11,000 --> 00:16:13,960
This is what the Upanishad tells us.

308
00:16:14,000 --> 00:16:16,960
Now, about the purity of food.

309
00:16:17,000 --> 00:16:18,960
The first thing we take in is food,

310
00:16:19,000 --> 00:16:20,960
and without food, we cannot survive.

311
00:16:21,000 --> 00:16:23,960
Therefore, giving food is considered very
good.

312
00:16:24,000 --> 00:16:26,960
But how do we determine if it is pure?

313
00:16:27,000 --> 00:16:30,960
There are certain qualities described for
that.

314
00:16:31,000 --> 00:16:34,960
One is called ja:thi dosha, a fault by the
food’s nature,

315
00:16:35,000 --> 00:16:39,960
and another is a:sraya dosha,

316
00:16:40,000 --> 00:16:45,960
which comes from who handles or associates
with it.

317
00:16:46,000 --> 00:16:51,960
If something falls in and spoils it
temporarily, that is called nimitta.

318
00:16:52,000 --> 00:17:01,960
Ja:thi, a:sraya, nimitta, adushta, annat,
ka:ya suddhi— [[REVIEW: non-Gi:tha do:sha terms run together; confirm wording + translation with a qualified scholar]]

319
00:17:02,000 --> 00:17:04,960
this discernment is called vivekam.

320
00:17:05,000 --> 00:17:07,960
It means we should not blame the food by
its ja:thi.

321
00:17:08,000 --> 00:17:11,960
Some items naturally have certain
qualities.

322
00:17:12,000 --> 00:17:16,960
Some are spicy, some are sour, and some
are sweet.

323
00:17:17,000 --> 00:17:19,960
These are their characteristics.

324
00:17:20,000 --> 00:17:23,960
In the same way, some are naturally
sa:thvic,

325
00:17:24,000 --> 00:17:25,960
some are naturally ra:jasic,

326
00:17:26,000 --> 00:17:27,960
and some are naturally tha:masic.

327
00:17:28,000 --> 00:17:29,960
That is how it is.

328
00:17:30,000 --> 00:17:39,960
Choose carefully what is sa:thvic by its
inherent nature.

329
00:17:40,000 --> 00:17:40,960
This inherent nature is called ja:thi.

330
00:17:41,000 --> 00:17:44,960
Do not allow anything of bad ja:thi to
enter you.

331
00:17:45,000 --> 00:17:46,960
That is why ja:thi matters.

332
00:17:47,000 --> 00:17:48,960
A:sraya.

333
00:17:49,000 --> 00:17:52,960
It depends on who handles it,

334
00:17:53,000 --> 00:17:56,000
and from whom it comes to you.

335
00:17:56,160 --> 00:18:00,920
The influence of that person can sometimes
affect the substance,

336
00:18:00,960 --> 00:18:07,920
especially if someone lacks proper
thinking,

337
00:18:07,960 --> 00:18:09,920
lacks firm resolve,

338
00:18:09,960 --> 00:18:11,920
and lacks the right qualification.

339
00:18:11,960 --> 00:18:17,920
We must ensure that by associating with
such people, this item does not get
spoiled.

340
00:18:17,960 --> 00:18:20,920
It should remain pure without being
tainted by their company.

341
00:18:20,960 --> 00:18:22,920
There are faults by association,

342
00:18:22,960 --> 00:18:24,920
faults by nature,

343
00:18:24,960 --> 00:18:26,920
faults by association,

344
00:18:26,960 --> 00:18:29,920
and faults by incidental cause.

345
00:18:29,960 --> 00:18:33,920
Nimitta means something temporarily
affects it,

346
00:18:33,960 --> 00:18:35,920
like something drops in for a moment.

347
00:18:35,960 --> 00:18:37,920
Maybe a worm fell in,

348
00:18:37,960 --> 00:18:39,920
or an ant fell in,

349
00:18:39,960 --> 00:18:41,960
or a hair fell in,

350
00:18:42,960 --> 00:18:51,920
These are temporary do:shas that arise
from such incidents.

351
00:18:51,960 --> 00:18:55,920
which is called nimitta do:sha.

352
00:18:55,960 --> 00:18:58,920
But a fault caused by nimitta is not truly
harmful.

353
00:18:58,960 --> 00:19:00,920
There is the fault by ja:thi,

354
00:19:00,960 --> 00:19:02,920
the fault by a:sraya,

355
00:19:02,960 --> 00:19:04,920
and the fault by nimitta,

356
00:19:04,960 --> 00:19:06,920
all related to food.

357
00:19:06,960 --> 00:19:15,920
If you take such food as nourishment for
the body,

358
00:19:15,960 --> 00:19:18,920
then the body becomes purified,

359
00:19:18,960 --> 00:19:25,920
your body will obey you as you command.

360
00:19:25,960 --> 00:19:29,920
When the body listens, the mind will also
listen.

361
00:19:29,960 --> 00:19:34,920
When the mind listens, a stream of jna:na
will flow.

362
00:19:34,960 --> 00:19:39,444
Jai Sri:manna:ra:yana! When the mind flows
steadily, the bondage of karma is

363
00:19:39,484 --> 00:19:39,920
removed.

364
00:19:39,960 --> 00:19:44,920
When that bondage is gone, what should be
seen within will become visible.

365
00:19:44,960 --> 00:19:48,920
The very first thing mentioned here is
vivekam, discernment.

366
00:19:48,960 --> 00:19:52,920
Make sure the food you eat is good and
pure.

367
00:19:52,960 --> 00:19:56,920
Our elders have taught this from worldly
experience.

368
00:19:56,960 --> 00:20:01,920
They said, if the food is good, the person
becomes strong and capable.

369
00:20:01,960 --> 00:20:04,920
Food must be wholesome.

370
00:20:04,960 --> 00:20:08,920
If you desire something, you will obtain
it.

371
00:20:08,960 --> 00:20:11,920
If you wish for strength, you will get
strength.

372
00:20:11,960 --> 00:20:13,920
If you wish for a head, you will get a
head.

373
00:20:13,960 --> 00:20:15,920
If you wish for intelligence, you will get
intelligence.

374
00:20:15,960 --> 00:20:18,920
Whatever you desire, you will receive it.

375
00:20:18,960 --> 00:20:24,920
So, food is very important.

376
00:20:24,960 --> 00:20:27,920
This discernment is called vive:kam.

377
00:20:27,960 --> 00:20:32,920
In the 2nd chapter, he tried to bring this
vivekam to fruition.

378
00:20:32,960 --> 00:20:35,920
In the 3rd chapter, he said,

379
00:20:35,960 --> 00:20:41,920
he explained what actions you must do with
that vive:kam.

380
00:20:41,960 --> 00:20:45,920
He called it Karma Yo:gam.

381
00:20:45,960 --> 00:20:47,920
We must do work,

382
00:20:47,960 --> 00:20:50,920
as the body is made to perform them.

383
00:20:50,960 --> 00:20:52,920
So it naturally engages in action.

384
00:20:52,960 --> 00:20:56,920
But you should know how to perform those
tasks properly.

385
00:20:56,960 --> 00:21:00,920
All those actions should be done with
clarity.

386
00:21:00,960 --> 00:21:04,920
Because it must be done, he called it
jna:nam.

387
00:21:04,960 --> 00:21:10,920
All actions should be refined by this
jna:nam.

388
00:21:10,960 --> 00:21:13,920
He mentioned this in the 3rd chapter.

389
00:21:13,960 --> 00:21:16,920
What is intelligence?

390
00:21:16,960 --> 00:21:18,920
That itself is a big question, isn't it?

391
00:21:18,960 --> 00:21:23,920
That intelligence must be free from desire
and resolve.

392
00:21:23,960 --> 00:21:27,920
He conveyed this in the 3rd chapter.

393
00:21:27,960 --> 00:21:31,920
It should have no kind of craving in it.

394
00:21:31,960 --> 00:21:35,920
You must not think, 'This is only for me.'

395
00:21:35,960 --> 00:21:38,920
yasya sarve: sama:rambha:ha,

396
00:21:38,960 --> 00:21:41,920
ka:ma sankalpa varjitha:ha.

397
00:21:41,960 --> 00:21:48,235
If we approach work without selfish
desires, three dangers arise: 'me',
'mine', and

398
00:21:48,275 --> 00:21:48,920
'for me'.

399
00:21:48,960 --> 00:21:51,920
One is thinking, 'I am doing it.'

400
00:21:51,960 --> 00:21:55,920
Another is believing, 'All this is because
of me.'

401
00:21:55,960 --> 00:21:58,920
These kinds of thoughts arise in us, don’t
they?

402
00:21:58,960 --> 00:22:06,920
But if you can perform your duty free from
such notions,

403
00:22:06,960 --> 00:22:10,920
that action becomes like a great
Agniho:tra,

404
00:22:10,960 --> 00:22:18,920
like a sacred fire that burns up the fuel
and impurities completely.

405
00:22:18,960 --> 00:22:23,920
Everything that you do is 'sarve
samarambhaha.'

406
00:22:23,960 --> 00:22:26,920
Whatever task you undertake at that
point...

407
00:22:26,960 --> 00:22:30,920
When done with the fire of jna:na, actions
gain noble impressions.

408
00:22:30,960 --> 00:22:34,920
If you act with this understanding, they
become purifying.

409
00:22:34,960 --> 00:22:36,920
So, give up attachments and do your
duties.

410
00:22:36,960 --> 00:22:42,920
Krishna never said to abandon the tasks
you must do.

411
00:22:42,960 --> 00:22:44,920
Krishna said this playfully — [[REVIEW: audio is "tama:sha: Krishnudu"; confirm exact sense]]

412
00:22:44,960 --> 00:22:47,920
did say to let go of what must be let go.

413
00:22:47,960 --> 00:22:49,920
So, what should we leave?

414
00:22:49,960 --> 00:22:54,920
Let go of the deep attachment to the
action itself.

415
00:22:54,960 --> 00:22:56,920
Now, perform your duties.

416
00:22:56,960 --> 00:22:59,920
What happens as a result?

417
00:22:59,960 --> 00:23:04,920
They burn away all obstacles like an
agni-hothram.

418
00:23:04,960 --> 00:23:07,920
They remove those hindrances completely.

419
00:23:07,960 --> 00:23:10,920
Now, start doing the tasks.

420
00:23:10,960 --> 00:23:14,920
He named these tasks as 'karma.'

421
00:23:14,960 --> 00:23:22,920
And the clear understanding free from
desire, he called 'jna:nam'.

422
00:23:22,960 --> 00:23:25,920
Now there is karma and there is jna:nam.

423
00:23:25,960 --> 00:23:27,920
There are two types.

424
00:23:27,960 --> 00:23:29,920
Karma must be practiced outwardly,

425
00:23:29,960 --> 00:23:31,920
while jna:nam is to be internalized.

426
00:23:31,960 --> 00:23:34,920
What is gained should remain steady.

427
00:23:34,960 --> 00:23:38,920
That steadiness should grow into firm
faith.

428
00:23:38,960 --> 00:23:41,920
That faith should be rooted in love.

429
00:23:41,960 --> 00:23:43,920
Then, you should carry out these tasks.

430
00:23:43,960 --> 00:23:50,920
Every action done this way brings joy to
the one who receives it.

431
00:23:50,960 --> 00:23:56,920
He mentioned that we should perform these
tasks in the third chapter.

432
00:23:56,960 --> 00:23:59,920
Bhagava:n showed us such a person.

433
00:23:59,960 --> 00:24:02,920
He gave him to us as Krishna.

434
00:24:02,960 --> 00:24:04,920
Today, He stands for us as the archaa
deity,

435
00:24:04,960 --> 00:24:09,920
in a form we can worship and serve.

436
00:24:09,960 --> 00:24:17,920
He taught us how to perform every task and
with what attitude.

437
00:24:17,960 --> 00:24:22,920
When Arjuna heard this, he felt compassion
for himself.

438
00:24:22,960 --> 00:24:24,920
he remained fixed in his own viewpoint,

439
00:24:24,960 --> 00:24:30,920
and did not readily accept what others
told him.

440
00:24:30,960 --> 00:24:36,920
He prefers to follow his own thoughts and
feelings.

441
00:24:36,960 --> 00:24:44,920
and does not even think, 'Let me listen
and reflect on what is said.'

442
00:24:44,960 --> 00:24:48,920
So he says we should do the work,

443
00:24:48,960 --> 00:24:52,920
but he emphasizes that intelligence is
crucial.

444
00:24:52,960 --> 00:24:56,920
If intelligence is primary, let us focus
on that.

445
00:24:56,960 --> 00:25:02,920
He feels content if we cease doing the
work.

446
00:25:02,960 --> 00:25:04,920
We should cease doing the work,

447
00:25:04,960 --> 00:25:06,920
and focus on knowledge.

448
00:25:06,960 --> 00:25:10,920
Now, there are two aspects, as we say,

449
00:25:10,960 --> 00:25:12,920
there is work and there is intelligence.

450
00:25:12,960 --> 00:25:14,920
There is karma and there is knowledge.

451
00:25:14,960 --> 00:25:17,920
Both action and jna:na are there, these
two exist.

452
00:25:17,960 --> 00:25:21,920
Now, how do we handle both of them?

453
00:25:21,960 --> 00:25:23,920
We must engage in action.

454
00:25:23,960 --> 00:25:25,920
Then, how should we do it?

455
00:25:25,960 --> 00:25:27,920
There must be strength from jna:na behind
it.

456
00:25:27,960 --> 00:25:29,920
What is important?

457
00:25:29,960 --> 00:25:31,920
Knowledge is very important.

458
00:25:31,960 --> 00:25:33,920
Oh, since jna:na is important, should we
stop acting?

459
00:25:33,960 --> 00:25:35,920
He is listening to the words,

460
00:25:35,960 --> 00:25:39,920
and he seems to understand them,

461
00:25:39,960 --> 00:25:41,920
but he does not have the chance to reflect
deeply

462
00:25:41,960 --> 00:25:50,920
and firmly establish them within himself.

463
00:25:50,960 --> 00:25:52,920
He's only partially understanding it.

464
00:25:52,960 --> 00:25:55,920
He is questioning himself if he has truly
understood it.

465
00:25:55,960 --> 00:26:01,920
Sri: Krishna is eager to make him
understand fully.

466
00:26:01,960 --> 00:26:03,920
That is how the third chapter concludes.

467
00:26:03,960 --> 00:26:07,920
He said, 'Jna:na is very important, dear
one.'

468
00:26:07,960 --> 00:26:09,920
He wanted to learn more about it.

469
00:26:09,960 --> 00:26:14,920
He explained the fourth chapter as well,

470
00:26:14,960 --> 00:26:17,920
He spoke about how crucial jna:na is.

471
00:26:17,960 --> 00:26:23,920
After all that, he said, 'Now that you
know its greatness...'

472
00:26:23,960 --> 00:26:25,920
'...stand up and do your duty.'

473
00:26:25,960 --> 00:26:27,920
Arjuna wonders, 'If jna:na is supreme, why
tell me to work again?'

474
00:26:27,960 --> 00:26:29,920
He repeats, 'Jna:na is great, yet you must
act.'

475
00:26:29,960 --> 00:26:31,644
If we think, ‘Since jna:na is supreme, let
us give up everything and sit in

476
00:26:31,684 --> 00:26:31,920
meditation’,

477
00:26:31,960 --> 00:26:38,175
then in the fourth chapter Bhagava:n says,
‘A:thishtta, yogam a:thishtta, utthishtta

478
00:26:38,215 --> 00:26:38,920
Bha:rata!’

479
00:26:38,960 --> 00:26:46,960
Now, is that jna:na or is it karma? Which
is it?

480
00:26:47,960 --> 00:26:51,920
I am unable to grasp which of the two is
truly right.

481
00:26:51,960 --> 00:26:55,920
Please clarify this for me.

482
00:26:55,960 --> 00:26:57,920
While we pray in this way,

483
00:26:57,960 --> 00:27:03,920
If we pray like this, the fifth chapter of
the Bhagavad Gi:tha begins.

484
00:27:03,960 --> 00:27:05,920
Let us understand the question,

485
00:27:05,960 --> 00:27:07,920
and let us know the answer.

486
00:27:07,960 --> 00:27:09,960
Jai Shri:man Na:ra:yana!
